                                 1.  INTRODUCTION
0             SCRIPT is a computer program  which accepts input,  proc-
+                                                         _____   ____
           esses it, and produces output.
+          _____                  ______
0             SCRIPT  recognizes only  two  different  types of  input:
           text and control  words.   The processing which  SCRIPT per-
+          ____     _______  _____
           forms is  called text formatting.    The output  produced by
+                           ____ __________
           SCRIPT is a document in which all  of the text has been for-
           matted according to the layout instructions specified by the
           control words.
-
-                             2.  CREATING THE INPUT
0             The input to  SCRIPT is a collection of  text and control
           words which you type at a typewriter terminal or visual-dis-
+                                    __________ ________    __________
           play terminal by  using a text editor.   A text  editor is a
+          ____ ________             ____ ______
           computer program which allows you to enter, correct, delete,
           add, and save the text and control words.
0             When you are entering the input, it is important that you
           start each sentence of the text  on a new input line.   This
           makes subsequent  insertions or deletions of  sentences much
           easier to perform.
-
           2.1   CONTROL WORDS AND TEXT
+                _______ _____ ___ ____
0             Each time  SCRIPT reads an input  line,  it looks  at the
           character in column 1.   If that character is a ".",  SCRIPT
           considers the input to be  a control word.   Otherwise,  the
           input line is treated as text.
0             Each SCRIPT control word is of the form
0               .xx operand(s)
0          The "." is  called the control word  indicator literal,  and
+                                                         _______
           "xx" is  a 2-character control  word.   Some  SCRIPT control
           words have one or more  operands.   The first operand begins
+                                  ________
           in the second position after the control word;  each operand
           is separated by a blank.
