           5.3   THE TEXT AREA
+                ___ ____ ____
0             The text area is that area  of the output page bounded on
           the  left by  the  left margin  (as  defined  by the  ADJUST
           value),  on the right by the right margin (as defined by the
           sum of the ADJUST and LINE LENGTH values plus 1), on the top
           by the top margin (as defined by the TOP MARGIN value),  and
           on the bottom by the bottom margin (as defined by the BOTTOM
           MARGIN value).
0             It is this "text area" into  which SCRIPT places its out-
           put lines.   Whenever the text area becomes full, SCRIPT au-
           tomatically skips to a new page.
